European Stocks Gain, Rebounding From 2 1/2 Month Low; U.S. Futures Rise

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-06-13T10:41:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/european-stocks-rise-from-2-1-2-month-low-as-enrc-shares-rally-on-bid-talk.html
European stocks rose, rebounding
from a 2 1/2 month low, as shares of Eurasian Natural Resources
Corp. advanced.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index rose 0.3 percent to
268.8 at 11:38 a.m. in  London  after earlier falling as much as
0.1 percent.  ENRC jumped 5.9 percent to 785.5 pence after the Sunday
Times reported that Glencore International Plc may make a bid
for the mining company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  